"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-alert-south-africa-wins-fourth-medal-at-paris-2024-paralympics-breaking-score\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbALERT: South Africa wins FOURTH medal at Paris 2024 Paralympics  Donald Ramphadi and Lucas Sithole combined to win South Africa's fourth medal at the Paris 2024 Paralympics on Wednesday.  Donald RamphadiandLucas Sitholecombined to win South Africa'sfourthmedal at theParis 2024 Paralympicson Wednesday.  For the latest Paris Paralympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  The duo picked up the bronze medal in theWheelchair Tennis\\u00a0Quad Doubles bronze medal matchagainst Brazilians\\u00a0pair Leandro Pena and Ymanitu Silva.  The South Africans defeated their Brazilian opponents6-2, 4-6, (10-8)in an absorbing match which lasted two hours and three minutes.  Ramphadi and Sithole are South Africa's first ever pair to clinch a medal in Wheelchair Tennis.  Earlier on Wednesday,Pieter du Preezwon South Africa's third medal.  Du Preez took the bronze medal\\u00a0in theH1 Individual Time Trialwhen he crossed the finish line in third place in a time of 36:07.05.  Italy's Fabrizio Cornegliani took gold in 34:50.45, while Maxime Hordies from Belgium took silver in 35:11.13.  Du Preez won the gold medal in the event at the most recent Paralympics held in Tokyo in 2021.  Meanwhile,Mpumelelo Mhlongowon goldin the men's T44 100m whileLouzanne Coetzeedoubled Team SA's medal tally\\u00a0when shewon the bronze medalin the 1 500m in the T11 class.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"